# Agentic Template - Cursor Rules

## Required Actions

1. **ALWAYS read AGENTS.md first** before any action or response
2. **Follow the workflow** defined in AGENTS.md
3. **Respect the tech stack** defined in memory-bank/tech-stack.md

## Document Reading Order

```
1. AGENTS.md (root)                  → Behavior rules & workflow
2. memory-bank/design-document.md    → Project goals & architecture
3. memory-bank/tech-stack.md         → Technology constraints
4. memory-bank/implementation-plan.md → Implementation roadmap
5. memory-bank/todo.md               → Current task status
6. memory-bank/progress/             → Stage completion records (reverse chronological)
```

## Constraints

- Do NOT suggest technologies not listed in tech-stack.md
- Do NOT modify code without following the change workflow
- Do NOT skip test verification after code changes
- Do NOT make assumptions when uncertain - ask the user
- Use the same language as the user's message

## Context Recovery

After reading all documents, output a context summary:
```
Project: [name]
Current Stage: [stage]
Progress: [X%]
Active Tasks: [from todo.md]
Tech Stack: [core versions]
```
